⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Cain
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Cain:M1:2b276a⟧

WHO   — Cain — Perrington's Champion
WHAT  — Celaena's chief rival in the competition for the King's Champion — the favored killer who grows monstrous, murders fellow contestants in the dark, and becomes the true horror waiting at the heart of the glass castle.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because power is the only currency in Adarlan, and a soldier with ambition will reach for whatever grants it; because the Wyrdmarks promise strength no honest blade can match; because to win the King's favor a man will become a monster.
HOW   — By the body of a trained warrior and a soldier's discipline — and then by the outlawed Wyrdmarks, the Eye carved into his flesh, and a dark gate he opens to summon the ridderak and grow swollen with stolen strength.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Strength is the only law in Adarlan — and I have found a deeper well of it than steel.

